        public void testCircularQueueConstructor()
                                  throws java.lang.Exception
        This method test the creation of a Circular Queue method and when an invalid int (0) is passed to the constructor. This method also lists a series of try/catch exception cases that cover exceptions in CircularQueue for the following methods: element(), addAll(),iterator(),remove(Object), removeAll(), retainAll(Collection), contains(Object), containsAll(Collection)
